The University of Calabar has announced Wednesday, Jan. 5, as the resumption date after the Christmas and New Year holidays. The announcement is contained in a statement signed by the Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Florence Obi, and made available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Calabar on Tuesday. “To this end, staff and students are expected back on campus to resume full academic and ancillary activities,” the statement added.   INEC releases Ekiti governorship election timetable     Police nab suspected ritualists in Bayelsa     JUST IN: Uzodimma fails to name sponsors of Imo crises   According to the statement, the management warmly welcomes the students back from the holiday. - Advertisement - It also expressed the hope that “the new year brings with it abundance of glad tidings, increased productivity and prosperity in an environment of harmonious coexistence”. (NAN)